Source: Field Guide to Native Edible Plants of NZ
Author: CROWE
Vol / Page: 149
Edition:
Quote: Neptune's necklace <i>Hormosira banksii</i>... A well-known seaweed up to 50 cm high, made up of pimply olive-brown hollow beads, each usually about 1 cm across. <i>Ibid.</i> 150 When the incidence of goitre was high in New Zealand, a schoolteacher here claimed to have appreciably reduced the goitre incidence in his school by getting the children to eat one 'bead' of Neptune's necklace a day.
